Class ListEventsMaxDistanceCommand

ICommand<java.util.List<Event>>
public class ListEventsMaxDistanceCommand
extends ListEventsCommand
ListEventsMaxDistanceCommand allows a logged in Consumer to generate a list of events within a given distance.

  • Constructor Details

    • ListEventsMaxDistanceCommand

      public ListEventsMaxDistanceCommand​(boolean userEventsOnly, boolean activeEventsOnly, java.time.LocalDate searchDate, TransportMode transportMode, double maxDistance)
      Parameters:
      userEventsOnly - if true, the returned events will be filtered depending on the logged-in user: for Staffs only the Events they have created, and for Consumers only the Events that match their EventTagCollection
      activeEventsOnly - if true, returned Events will be filtered to contain only Events with EventStatus.ACTIVE
      searchDate - chosen date to look for events. Can be null. If not null, only Events that are happening on ListEventsCommand.searchDate (i.e., starting, ending, or in between) will be included
      transportMode - mode of transportation to calculate distance for
      maxDistance - maximum distance of each Event from the Consumer's address
